A vintage 1970s corporate office photograph with warm sepia tones and film grain, showing five empty office chairs arranged in a circle around a cluttered desk piled high with papers, coffee cups, and scattered documents. Each chair is turned slightly away from the desk, as if their occupants simultaneously fled. Through a large window, a single person is visible outside on a park bench reading a newspaper. Dust motes float in the afternoon sunlight streaming through venetian blinds, casting striped shadows across the abandoned workspace. The scene evokes quiet absurdity and gentle cynicism about collaborative work culture.
